# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: NeitherPath2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Nearly a week had passed since Sarah learned of Marion's betrayal."
    new "Nearly a week had passed since Sarah learned of Marion's betrayal."

    old "Sarah kept court as best she could, handing down her instructions to the different members of her council."
    new "Sarah kept court as best she could, handing down her instructions to the different members of her council."

    old "Her first goal was to understand the impacts of the uprising, and over the course of days, it had slowly become clear."
    new "Her first goal was to understand the impacts of the uprising, and over the course of days, it had slowly become clear."

    old "Whilst the old houses had betrayed her, most of the nobility still stood with the Rose family."
    new "Whilst the old houses had betrayed her, most of the nobility still stood with the Rose family."

    old "Though this gave Sarah some space to breathe, the truth was that the five old houses held nearly as much power as all the other noble families combined."
    new "Though this gave Sarah some space to breathe, the truth was that the five old houses held nearly as much power as all the other noble families combined."

    old "As a result, Rosanna had lost a great deal of its military power and the nation's economy had been thrown a state of disarray."
    new "As a result, Rosanna had lost a great deal of its military power and the nation's economy had been thrown a state of disarray."

    old "The military reports slowly painted an increasingly clear picture."
    new "The military reports slowly painted an increasingly clear picture."

    old "The old houses were gathering their forces near the western province of Dianthus, the ancestral seat of power of the Achillea family."
    new "The old houses were gathering their forces near the western province of Dianthus, the ancestral seat of power of the Achillea family."

    old "The borders of the province were carved out by a strong river, which made for a natural defence."
    new "The borders of the province were carved out by a strong river, which made for a natural defence."

    old "The river also sprang from the neighbouring country of Normandi."
    new "The river also sprang from the neighbouring country of Normandi."

    old "As a result, not only was it impossible for Rosanna to cut off supplies to her enemy, in fact, it was her enemy who was now cutting off supplies to her."
    new "As a result, not only was it impossible for Rosanna to cut off supplies to her enemy, in fact, it was her enemy who was now cutting off supplies to her."

    old "Sarah had contacted the queen of Normandi, Queen Maeiv."
    new "Sarah had contacted the queen of Normandi, Queen Maeiv."

    old "Queen Maeiv ruled the neighbouring country of Normandi. Under her rule, the two countries had existed in a relative peace."
    new "Queen Maeiv ruled the neighbouring country of Normandi. Under her rule, the two countries had existed in a relative peace."

    old "This was not to say that their nations were allies, but they had managed to put their history of war to a rest."
    new "This was not to say that their nations were allies, but they had managed to put their history of war to a rest."

    old "Sarah had urged her to block trade downstream from the river, preventing Marion's forces from being able to supply themselves."
    new "Sarah had urged her to block trade downstream from the river, preventing Marion's forces from being able to supply themselves."

    old "In truth, Sarah had asked her even more. She asked her to send an army to help her in crushing this rebellion, but as Sarah had expected, this demand was too much."
    new "In truth, Sarah had asked her even more. She asked her to send an army to help her in crushing this rebellion, but as Sarah had expected, this demand was too much."

    old "Queen Maeiv agreed to block up the river, but refused to send her armies. She had offered up an excuse, but in truth, Sarah knew that she would receive no aid."
    new "Queen Maeiv agreed to block up the river, but refused to send her armies. She had offered up an excuse, but in truth, Sarah knew that she would receive no aid."

    old "Sarah's position was still weak. She understood that Maeiv was simply refusing to commit herself to either side, so that she could be friendly with whichever side ended up winning."
    new "Sarah's position was still weak. She understood that Maeiv was simply refusing to commit herself to either side, so that she could be friendly with whichever side ended up winning."

    old "Still, with the river blocked up, Marion's troops would have a harder time to remain on the field."
    new "Still, with the river blocked up, Marion's troops would have a harder time to remain on the field."

    old "Which also meant they would be more desperate to strike out before their supplies dwindled."
    new "Which also meant they would be more desperate to strike out before their supplies dwindled."

    old "At every turn, Sarah saw the strategy shift and change. Each solution posed new problems."
    new "At every turn, Sarah saw the strategy shift and change. Each solution posed new problems."

    old "Sitting atop the throne, it was exactly such a new problem that came before Sarah."
    new "Sitting atop the throne, it was exactly such a new problem that came before Sarah."

    old "Princess Sarah."
    new "Princess Sarah."

    old "Kravel had approached the throne."
    new "Kravel had approached the throne."

    old "Do you have news for me, spymaster?"
    new "Do you have news for me, spymaster?"

    old "News of a sort, Princess."
    new "News of a sort, Princess."

    old "He motioned towards the end of the room."
    new "He motioned towards the end of the room."

    old "Sarah watched as a series of people, linked together with a chain, were brought into the room."
    new "Sarah watched as a series of people, linked together with a chain, were brought into the room."

    old "Each tied by hand and by feet to the next."
    new "Each tied by hand and by feet to the next."

    old "It took her a moment to realize, these were more children than adults. The oldest near the front was a woman, but even she was only Sarah's age, twenty or so, she estimated."
    new "It took her a moment to realize, these were more children than adults. The oldest near the front was a woman, but even she was only Sarah's age, twenty or so, she estimated."

    old "We caught these people trying to sneak out of the capital."
    new "We caught these people trying to sneak out of the capital."

    old "Sarah eyed the prisoners."
    new "Sarah eyed the prisoners."

    old "She wondered how they could have done much of anything. Some of them were no older than six."
    new "She wondered how they could have done much of anything. Some of them were no older than six."

    old "They are members of the Highfield family."
    new "They are members of the Highfield family."

    old "Sarah was surprised to learn this. The Highfield family was one of the old houses that turned against her, but for them to leave their children behind seemed odd."
    new "Sarah was surprised to learn this. The Highfield family was one of the old houses that turned against her, but for them to leave their children behind seemed odd."

    old "In addition, Sarah knew the Highfield family well, and none of the people before her were familiar."
    new "In addition, Sarah knew the Highfield family well, and none of the people before her were familiar."

    old "The Highfield family is led by five brothers. They don't have any sisters. So if this is the Highfield family, who is she?"
    new "The Highfield family is led by five brothers. They don't have any sisters. So if this is the Highfield family, who is she?"

    old "Kravel seemed to pause for a moment."
    new "Kravel seemed to pause for a moment."

    old "Well, uhm, Princess Sarah...they are-"
    new "Well, uhm, Princess Sarah...they are-"

    old "The girl at the head of the chain gang interrupted Kravel."
    new "The girl at the head of the chain gang interrupted Kravel."

    old "What your moronic spymaster is trying to tell you is that we're not Highfielders...well, not really."
    new "What your moronic spymaster is trying to tell you is that we're not Highfielders...well, not really."

    old "Sarah was only geting more confused."
    new "Sarah was only geting more confused."

    old "What does she mean, Kravel?"
    new "What does she mean, Kravel?"

    old "Well, she is right, and wrong, in a way."
    new "Well, she is right, and wrong, in a way."

    old "Theirs is a minor branch of the Highfield family. The Highfield brothers have an uncle, whose second wife..."
    new "Theirs is a minor branch of the Highfield family. The Highfield brothers have an uncle, whose second wife..."

    old "Sarah waved her hand to dismiss him."
    new "Sarah waved her hand to dismiss him."

    old "Fine, I understand."
    new "Fine, I understand."

    old "Rosanna had countless noble families, and even the great families had small offshoots that were royal in name, but who bore no lands and little wealth."
    new "Rosanna had countless noble families, and even the great families had small offshoots that were royal in name, but who bore no lands and little wealth."

    old "So why did you bring them here?"
    new "So why did you bring them here?"

    old "Princess Sarah, we can use these people as leverage."
    new "Princess Sarah, we can use these people as leverage."

    old "The Highfield family will not wish any harm come to them or their children. Just as they keep King Thomas as a hostage, we can keep them, to make certain nothing happens to your brother."
    new "The Highfield family will not wish any harm come to them or their children. Just as they keep King Thomas as a hostage, we can keep them, to make certain nothing happens to your brother."

    old "The girl near the front began to laugh."
    new "The girl near the front began to laugh."

    old "You think my stupid fucking nephews give a shit about me or any of my brothers and sisters?"
    new "You think my stupid fucking nephews give a shit about me or any of my brothers and sisters?"

    old "We're lucky to be invited once a year to their estate, hells, some year they even forget to invite us at all."
    new "We're lucky to be invited once a year to their estate, hells, some year they even forget to invite us at all."

    old "They're not going to give a damn if you hang us or not. Gods, they might actually thank you for getting rid of us!"
    new "They're not going to give a damn if you hang us or not. Gods, they might actually thank you for getting rid of us!"

    old "Sarah could see Kravel grow increasingly annoyed."
    new "Sarah could see Kravel grow increasingly annoyed."

    old "The girl will say whatever to keep her life. They are Highfielders; their lives hold value."
    new "The girl will say whatever to keep her life. They are Highfielders; their lives hold value."

    old "We can keep them in the dungeon and I will let our enemy know that we hold this leverage over them."
    new "We can keep them in the dungeon and I will let our enemy know that we hold this leverage over them."

    old "The girl near the front of the prisoners stepped forward, as far as the chain would allow her."
    new "The girl near the front of the prisoners stepped forward, as far as the chain would allow her."

    old "Princess Sarah!"
    new "Princess Sarah!"

    old "My name is Lily Highfield, and I swear on everything in heaven, here on earth and everything down in hell, that I knew nothing of my family and their dishonesty."
    new "My name is Lily Highfield, and I swear on everything in heaven, here on earth and everything down in hell, that I knew nothing of my family and their dishonesty."

    old "They left me and my brothers and sisters behind in the capital to face a punishment for their crimes, but we are innocent."
    new "They left me and my brothers and sisters behind in the capital to face a punishment for their crimes, but we are innocent."

    old "We have never met, but all the stories I have heard about you tell me that you are a kind and merciful ruler."
    new "We have never met, but all the stories I have heard about you tell me that you are a kind and merciful ruler."

    old "I offer you my life!"
    new "I offer you my life!"

    old "If you spare my brothers and sisters, I will bend my knee and serve you as a knight."
    new "If you spare my brothers and sisters, I will bend my knee and serve you as a knight."

    old "Sarah looked over the prisoners. Children, if she was being honest."
    new "Sarah looked over the prisoners. Children, if she was being honest."

    old "The dungeon was a cruel place for an adult, she feared what it might do to those too small to even understand why they'd be kept there."
    new "The dungeon was a cruel place for an adult, she feared what it might do to those too small to even understand why they'd be kept there."

    old "And yet...wasn't she at war?"
    new "And yet...wasn't she at war?"

    old "Didn't she need to steel her heart and be as cruel to her enemies as they were to her? Did Marion worry about keeping Thomas in chains?"
    new "Didn't she need to steel her heart and be as cruel to her enemies as they were to her? Did Marion worry about keeping Thomas in chains?"

    old "But another voice spoke to her, that of her father."
    new "But another voice spoke to her, that of her father."

    old "What was the point of victory, if she was no different than her enemies?"
    new "What was the point of victory, if she was no different than her enemies?"

    old "Let them go."
    new "Let them go."

    old "Sarah looked over them."
    new "Sarah looked over them."

    old "They were children, and she did not have the heart to even hurt one hair on their heads, let alone keep them as hostages."
    new "They were children, and she did not have the heart to even hurt one hair on their heads, let alone keep them as hostages."

    old "Let them go, Kravel."
    new "Let them go, Kravel."

    old "Cut their chains and set them free. This is pointless."
    new "Cut their chains and set them free. This is pointless."

    old "We can't go around capturing or killing anyone that bears a royal name. We'd be no better than Marion and his gang."
    new "We can't go around capturing or killing anyone that bears a royal name. We'd be no better than Marion and his gang."

    old "Kravel bowed his head in deference to her decision, but she doubted he fully supported it."
    new "Kravel bowed his head in deference to her decision, but she doubted he fully supported it."

    old "As instructed, the soldiers began to cut the chains off the prisoners."
    new "As instructed, the soldiers began to cut the chains off the prisoners."

    old "Lily Highfield stepped forward and approache the throne, falling down onto one knee."
    new "Lily Highfield stepped forward and approache the throne, falling down onto one knee."

    old "My vow was not an idle promise. I vow to serve you as loyal as any knight ever could."
    new "My vow was not an idle promise. I vow to serve you as loyal as any knight ever could."

    old "Sarah looked at the girl. She seemed entirely serious."
    new "Sarah looked at the girl. She seemed entirely serious."

    old "Please, Lily, rise. You spoke your words under threat of imprisonment. Do not feel any obligation to keep your vow."
    new "Please, Lily, rise. You spoke your words under threat of imprisonment. Do not feel any obligation to keep your vow."

    old "The girl shook her head."
    new "The girl shook her head."

    old "I did, but let me utter them again, free of duress! I will serve you, loyally, forever!"
    new "I did, but let me utter them again, free of duress! I will serve you, loyally, forever!"

    old "My family betrayed you. Give me a chance, and I will work a lifetime to clean their dishonesty from my family's name!"
    new "My family betrayed you. Give me a chance, and I will work a lifetime to clean their dishonesty from my family's name!"

    old "I was trained from a young age in martial combat. I know how to wield a sword. Please allow me to server your family as the rest of my clan failed to do."
    new "I was trained from a young age in martial combat. I know how to wield a sword. Please allow me to server your family as the rest of my clan failed to do."

    old "Sarah studied her a while longer."
    new "Sarah studied her a while longer."

    old "To deny her now would be an insult to her chivalry. Perhaps there was wisdom in keeping a Highfield in her service. Show others that there was mercy to those who were loyal."
    new "To deny her now would be an insult to her chivalry. Perhaps there was wisdom in keeping a Highfield in her service. Show others that there was mercy to those who were loyal."

    old "Very well, Lily Highfield."
    new "Very well, Lily Highfield."

    old "By my word, I grant you the title of knighthood, on the grounds that you swear to offer up your life to me and my family, from this day until your last."
    new "By my word, I grant you the title of knighthood, on the grounds that you swear to offer up your life to me and my family, from this day until your last."

    old "I swear!"
    new "I swear!"

    old "And with that, the girl rose up and the ceremony was complete."
    new "And with that, the girl rose up and the ceremony was complete."

    old "The other members of her family were escorted out by the soldiers, but Lily remained."
    new "The other members of her family were escorted out by the soldiers, but Lily remained."

    old "Sarah hoped she had made the right decision."
    new "Sarah hoped she had made the right decision."

    old "Keep them as our hostages."
    new "Keep them as our hostages."

    old "She rememberd Thomas, and knew she would need any possible advantage she could get to bring him home safe."
    new "She rememberd Thomas, and knew she would need any possible advantage she could get to bring him home safe."

    old "It pained her heart to do this, but if it meant improving her odds of saving Thomas, she would do it."
    new "It pained her heart to do this, but if it meant improving her odds of saving Thomas, she would do it."

    old "Kravel, take them to our dungeon."
    new "Kravel, take them to our dungeon."

    old "No! Please! You can't do this!"
    new "No! Please! You can't do this!"

    old "Their cries were cut short as the soldiers dragged them away."
    new "Their cries were cut short as the soldiers dragged them away."

    old "Sarah could see in Kravel's face that he approved of her decision."
    new "Sarah could see in Kravel's face that he approved of her decision."

    old "Still, Sarah could not help but feel a sting of pain."
    new "Still, Sarah could not help but feel a sting of pain."

    old "Was this what it meant to be a ruler? To ruin one's own heart in the pursuit of their own interests?"
    new "Was this what it meant to be a ruler? To ruin one's own heart in the pursuit of their own interests?"

    old "Sarah thought of her father, and wondered if he had ever been forced to make such cruel decisions. Did they weigh on him as they now weighed on her?"
    new "Sarah thought of her father, and wondered if he had ever been forced to make such cruel decisions. Did they weigh on him as they now weighed on her?"

    old "She cleared her mind."
    new "She cleared her mind."

    old "It was done, no point wasting more time on it."
    new "It was done, no point wasting more time on it."

    old "Hang them. Send a message."
    new "Hang them. Send a message."

    old "She remembered Thomas, and how others sought to play on her weak heart. Never again."
    new "She remembered Thomas, and how others sought to play on her weak heart. Never again."

    old "Hang them from the castle gates."
    new "Hang them from the castle gates."

    old "Let everyone in the capital knows what happens to those who betray my family."
    new "Let everyone in the capital knows what happens to those who betray my family."

    old "A wailing sound began to break out among those old enough to understand what was about to happen."
    new "A wailing sound began to break out among those old enough to understand what was about to happen."

    old "Sarah imagined she could see a moment of hesitation, even in the face of Kravel."
    new "Sarah imagined she could see a moment of hesitation, even in the face of Kravel."

    old "But none objected, and so her will was carried out."
    new "But none objected, and so her will was carried out."

    old "Before the sun was down, more than a dozen corpses swung from a rope on Castle Reinmeer."
    new "Before the sun was down, more than a dozen corpses swung from a rope on Castle Reinmeer."

    old "Whispers among the people spread far and wide."
    new "Whispers among the people spread far and wide."

    old "If it was fear that Sarah hoped to instill, she had sown it far and wide."
    new "If it was fear that Sarah hoped to instill, she had sown it far and wide."

    old "Sarah stood up and walked away from the throne room."
    new "Sarah stood up and walked away from the throne room."

    old "It had been a long day, and she could bear no more."
    new "It had been a long day, and she could bear no more."

